OL,3,CPressure on Starmer ramps up as
OL,4,CBurnham one step closer to challenge
OL,6,FBut Mr Burnham could benefit from his
OL,7,Fstrong personal following across the
OL,8,FNorth West, where he enjoys a net
OL,9,Ffavourability rating of 24% according
OL,10,Fto pollster Ipsos ` considerably
OL,11,Fhigher than any of the party leaders
OL,12,For the Labour Party itself.
OL,14,FA Survation forecast suggested that
OL,15,Fwith Mr Burnham as a candidate, Labour
OL,16,Fis more likely to win than Reform UK,
OL,17,Fbut without him, Mr Farage's party is
OL,18,Flikely to take the seat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
