OL,3,CPressure on Starmer ramps up as
OL,4,CBurnham one step closer to challenge
OL,6,FBut an unnamed Cabinet minister loyal
OL,7,Fto Sir Keir described the Prime
OL,8,FMinister as much less categorical
OL,9,Fabout his future in private, telling
OL,10,FThe Telegraph he was keeping "all
OL,11,Foptions" open.
OL,13,FThe Times has reported that Sir Keir
OL,14,Fcould approve an #18 billion boost to
OL,15,Fdefence spending next week as he
OL,16,Fbattles to save his premiership.
OL,26,@rD@^OUsD@HO]
